To test this, I started with this big template:
{code}
{
  "Resources" : {
    "S3Bucket" : {
      "Type" : "AWS::S3::Bucket",
      "Properties" : {
        "AccessControl" : "PublicRead",
        "BucketName" : "PublicBucket",
        "VersioningConfiguration" : {"Status" : "Enabled"},
        "NotificationConfiguration": {
          "TopicConfigurations": [
            {
              "Topic": "arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:123456789012:TestTopic",
              "Event": "s3:ReducedRedundancyLostObject"
            } 
          ]
        }, 
        "WebsiteConfiguration" : {
          "IndexDocument" : "index.html",
          "ErrorDocument" : "error.html",
          "RoutingRules": [
            {
              "RoutingRuleCondition": {
                "HttpErrorCodeReturnedEquals": "404",
                "KeyPrefixEquals": "out1/"
              },
              "RedirectRule": {
                "HostName": "ec2-11-22-333-44.compute-1.amazonaws.com",
                "ReplaceKeyPrefixWith": "report-404/"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "ReplicationConfiguration": {
          "Role": "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/replication_role",
          "Rules": [
            {
              "Id": "MyRule1",
              "Status": "Enabled",
              "Prefix": "MyPrefix",
              "Destination": {
                "Bucket": "arn:aws:s3:::my-replication-bucket",
                "StorageClass": "STANDARD"
              }
            },
            {
              "Status": "Enabled",
              "Prefix": "MyOtherPrefix",
              "Destination": {
                "Bucket": "arn:aws:s3:::my-replication-bucket"
              }
            }
          ]
        },

        "CorsConfiguration": {
          "CorsRules": [
            {
              "AllowedHeaders": [
                "*"
              ],
              "AllowedMethods": [
                "GET"
              ],
              "AllowedOrigins": [
                "*"
              ],
              "ExposedHeaders": [
                "Date"
              ],
              "Id": "myCORSRuleId1",
              "MaxAge": "3600"
            },
            {
              "AllowedHeaders": [
                "x-amz-*"
              ],
              "AllowedMethods": [
                "DELETE"
              ],
              "AllowedOrigins": [
                "http://www.example1.com",
                "http://www.example2.com"
              ],
              "ExposedHeaders": [
                "Connection",
                "Server",
                "Date"
              ],
              "Id": "myCORSRuleId2",
              "MaxAge": "1800"
            } 
          ]
        },
        "LifecycleConfiguration": {
          "Rules": [
            {
              "Id": "GlacierRule",
              "Prefix": "glacier",
              "Status": "Enabled",
              "ExpirationInDays": "365",
              "Transition": {
                "TransitionInDays": "1",
                "StorageClass": "Glacier"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "LoggingConfiguration": {
          "DestinationBucketName": {"Ref" : "LoggingBucket"},
          "LogFilePrefix": "testing-logs"
        },
        "Tags" : [{"Key":"Hi","Value":"There"}]
      }
    },
    "LoggingBucket": {
      "Type": "AWS::S3::Bucket",
      "Properties": {
        "AccessControl": "LogDeliveryWrite"
      }
    }
  },

  "Outputs" : {
    "WebsiteURL" : {
      "Value" : { "Fn::GetAtt" : [ "S3Bucket", "WebsiteURL" ] },
      "Description" : "URL for website hosted on S3"
    },
    "S3BucketSecureURL" : {
      "Value" : { "Fn::Join" : [ "", [ "https://", { "Fn::GetAtt" : [ "S3Bucket", "DomainName" ] } ] ] },
      "Description" : "Name of S3 bucket to hold website content"
    },
    "BucketName": {
      "Value": {
        "Ref": "S3Bucket"
      },
      "Description": "Name of the sample Amazon S3 bucket with a lifecycle configuration."
    }
  }
}
{code}
1) I tried to create this stack.  There are several issues.  We do not support LoggingConfiguration, NotificationConfiguration, WebsiteConfiguration, or ReplicationConfiguration.  We also do not support LifecycleConfiguration at the same time as VersioningConfiguration.  Finally, we do not support uppercase bucket names.  Creating stack should fail with one of these errors until everything is done.
It failed in the following order.  (Before each, I tried to create the stack)
2) "Unable to set both lifecycle configuration and versioning configuration for buckets".  Deleted stack and removed the "VersioningConfiguration" of the first bucket.
3) "Bucket name should not contain uppercase characters".  Deleted stack, and changed first bucket name to "publicbucket".
4) "LoggingConfiguration not yet implemented".  Deleted stack, removed LoggingConfiguration section from the first bucket, and removed the second bucket entirely.
5) "NotificationConfiguration not yet implemented".  Deleted stack, removed NotificationConfiguration section from the first bucket.
6) "ReplicationConfiguration not yet implemented".  Deleted stack, removed ReplicationConfiguration section from the first bucket.
7) "WebsiteConfiguration not yet implemented".  Deleted stack, removed WebsiteConfiguration section from the first bucket.
8) Created stack, finally works.  Final template for creation looks like this.
