9) Try to update the new template to the original template.  Got the same errors in the same order as during create: "Unable to set both lifecycle configuration and versioning configuration for buckets", "Bucket name should not contain uppercase characters", "LoggingConfiguration not yet implemented", "NotificationConfiguration not yet implemented", "ReplicationConfiguration not yet implemented", "WebsiteConfiguration not yet implemented".  Ended up with the same stack.  Verify all fields go through.  (May need aws sdk).  At the moment cors goes thru but there is an issue with getBucketConfiguration() which should be fixed soon.  (Outside the scope of Cloudformation).
10) Start with the new stack (as shown above), remove the Access Control value. Update.  New value should be Full Control
11) Add the access control value back, re-update.  Make sure the value is correct.
12) Modify some tags, update the stack.  Make sure the value goes thru.
13) Mofify some cors rules.  Make sure the value is updated.
14) Delete the lifecycle configuration and try to add a version.  Should work the first time.
15) Try to delete the version and add a lifecycle configuration.  Should not work as can not do lifecycle any time after versioning.
16) Change the bucket name.  Make sure a new bucket exists and the old one is gone.
17) Update versioning to Enabled, update stack.  Remove versioning, update stack.  Version should be suspended.
